title: 青云-8888
content:
青云-8888
2m
Follow
See original
Japan's first compliant yen stablecoin has officially launched.

Recently, the Japanese startup JPYC officially launched the stablecoin JPYC, which is pegged to the yen at a 1:1 ratio. This is not only an important milestone in the development of digital currency in Japan but also provides a localized alternative to US dollar stablecoins for the Asian region.

This stablecoin has several key features:
· Fully compliant operation: JPYC completed registration with the Japanese Financial Services Agency in August this year, becoming a fund transfer service provider and fully complying with Japan's 2023 revised stablecoin regulations.
· Reliable asset backing: Guaranteed by yen savings and Japanese government bonds, ensuring that each JPYC is backed by adequate assets.
· Multi-chain deployment: Issued simultaneously on three mainstream public chains: Avalanche, Ethereum, and Polygon.
· Low entry threshold: Users only need to complete identity verification using the My Number card to directly purchase on the JPYC EX platform.

What does this mean for the market?
Currently, the global stablecoin market is dominated by US dollar stablecoins, accounting for over 99%. The launch of JPYC will provide Asian users with options that better meet local needs, helping to reduce excessive dependence on the US dollar.

It is worth mentioning that JPYC waives transaction fees during the promotional period, with the company primarily profiting from the interest earned on government bonds. They have set quite an ambitious goal: to achieve a circulation scale of 100 trillion yen (approximately 65.4 billion USD) within three years.

As Japan improves its regulatory framework for digital currencies, the launch of this first compliant yen stablecoin will undoubtedly bring new vitality and possibilities to the Asian digital currency market.
